"```sql\nSELECT \n  (SUM(CASE WHEN Date LIKE '1981-11-%' THEN T-CHO ELSE 0 END) - \n   SUM(CASE WHEN Date LIKE '1981-12-%' THEN T-CHO ELSE 0 END)) AS decrease_rate\nFROM \n  Laboratory\nJOIN \n  Patient ON Laboratory.ID = Patient.ID\nWHERE \n  Patient.Birthday = '1959-02-18';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the decrease rate of total cholesterol (T-CHO) for a patient born on February 18, 1959, by subtracting the sum of T-CHO values in December 1981 from the sum of T-CHO values in November 1981. The query joins the Laboratory and Patient tables using the foreign key relationship between their ID columns."